description:
correct：
mysql> select * from t1 where col1 like "amysql%";
+--------+------+
| col1   | col2 |
+--------+------+
| amysql
 | b    |
+--------+------+
1 row in set (0.04 sec)

incorrect：
mysql> select * from t1 where col1 like "amysql%";
Empty set
How to repeat:
create table t1(col1 varchar(255) COLLATE utf8_bin DEFAULT NULL, col2 varchar(255) COLLATE utf8_bin DEFAULT NULL, KEY `Idx_col1` (col1))ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=9 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8 COLLATE=utf8_bin;

insert into t1 values("a","b");

update t1 set col1 = "amysql\r\n" where col2 = "b";
